<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06339240 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06339240 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  A 40-year-old San Jose man remained in very serious condition Tuesday after hewas shot Monday night in front of his home in the 4000 block of San BernardinoWay off Senter Road. Michael Meek was taken to San Jose Medical Center withwounds in his torso and a leg. According to police, Meek told his wife at 10p.m. that he was going to the store. A few minutes later, police said, someonecame to the door and told the family Meek had been shot and was lying in thestreet not far from their front door. Witnesses told police they saw a small,dark-colored pickup speed off. Investigators have not found a reason for theshooting. Anyone with information is asked to contact the assault unit at(408) 277-4161.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  S.J. MAN SHOT NEAR HIS HOME; MOTIVE SOUGHT  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Bay Area in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911204  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  December  </MONTH><PG.COL>  5B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  139  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday, December 4, 199100339240,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>